OL,3,CPublic toilets under threat in
OL,4,CEastbourne as council tries to save
OL,5,Cmoney
OL,7,FAbigail Bracken's report from
OL,8,FEastbourne
OL,10,FThousands have signed a petition
OL,11,Fagainst closing public toilets on
OL,12,FEastbourne seafront, as campaigners
OL,13,Fsay loos are an essential service that
OL,14,Fno one can do without.
OL,16,FEastbourne Council is consulting on
OL,17,Fplans to move towards a community
OL,18,Ftoilet scheme - to save money - and
OL,19,Fhas only committed to running one loo
OL,20,Fon the seafront.
