OL,3,CPublic toilets under threat in
OL,4,CEastbourne as council tries to save
OL,5,Cmoney
OL,7,FThis comes as public toilets have been
OL,8,Fshutting nationwide. The British
OL,9,FToilet Association estimates there are
OL,10,Fnow up to 60% fewer public toilets
OL,11,Fthan in 2010.
OL,13,FCampaigners say that closing loos in
OL,14,FEastbourne will particularly affect
OL,15,Fthe elderly, those with children,
OL,16,Fmedical needs and the disabled.
